Database Schema Design for AniCrave
This document outlines the proposed database structure for AniCrave, designed to support users, anime data, and interactions like favorites and (potential) reviews.

1. Relational Schema (SQL)
Suitable for PostgreSQL, MySQL, or SQLite.

users
Stores user account information.

Column	Type	Constraints	Description
id	UUID / INT	PK, Auto-increment	Unique user identifier
username	VARCHAR(50)	UNIQUE, NOT NULL	User's display name
email	VARCHAR(255)	UNIQUE, NOT NULL	User's email address
password_hash	VARCHAR(255)	NOT NULL	Hashed password
created_at	TIMESTAMP	DEFAULT NOW()	Account creation time
avatar_url	VARCHAR(255)	NULL	Profile picture URL
anime
Stores static information about anime titles.

Column	Type	Constraints	Description
id	INT	PK	Unique anime identifier
title	VARCHAR(255)	NOT NULL	Main title
description	TEXT	NULL	Synopsis
cover_image_url	VARCHAR(255)	NULL	URL to cover image
banner_image_url	VARCHAR(255)	NULL	URL to banner image
format	VARCHAR(20)	NULL	TV, Movie, OVA, etc.
episodes	INT	NULL	Total episode count
episode_duration	INT	NULL	Duration in minutes
status	VARCHAR(20)	NULL	Finished, Releasing, Not Yet Aired
season	VARCHAR(20)	NULL	Fall, Winter, Spring, Summer
year	INT	NULL	Release year
start_date	DATE	NULL	Premiere date
studios	VARCHAR(100)	NULL	Comma-separated or referenced table
average_score	INT	NULL	e.g. 91 (percentage)
genres
Lookup table for genres.

Column	Type	Constraints	Description
id	INT	PK	Unique genre ID
name	VARCHAR(50)	UNIQUE, NOT NULL	Genre name (Adventure, Fantasy)
anime_genres
Many-to-Many relationship between Anime and Genres.

Column	Type	Constraints	Description
anime_id	INT	FK -> anime.id	
genre_id	INT	FK -> genres.id	
PK		(anime_id, genre_id)	Composite Primary Key
favorites (or user_anime_list)
Tracks which anime users have bookmarked/favorited.

Column	Type	Constraints	Description
user_id	UUID / INT	FK -> users.id	
anime_id	INT	FK -> anime.id	
status	VARCHAR(20)	DEFAULT 'Planning'	Watching, Completed, Planning, Dropped
is_favorite	BOOLEAN	DEFAULT FALSE	"Hearted" status
created_at	TIMESTAMP	DEFAULT NOW()	When added to list
PK		(user_id, anime_id)	
2. NoSQL Structure (JSON / MongoDB)
Suitable for flexible schemas or rapid prototyping.

users Collection
{
  "_id": "user_123",
  "username": "AnimeFan99",
  "email": "fan@example.com",
  "password_hash": "...",
  "created_at": "2024-01-01T12:00:00Z",
  "favorites": [ // Array of Anime IDs or Objects
    {
      "anime_id": "anime_456",
      "added_at": "2024-01-02T10:00:00Z"
    }
  ]
}
anime Collection
{
  "_id": "anime_456",
  "title": "Frieren: Beyond Journey's End",
  "description": "...",
  "cover_image": "...",
  "details": {
    "format": "TV",
    "episodes": 28,
    "season": "Fall",
    "year": 2023,
    "studios": ["Madhouse"],
    "genres": ["Adventure", "Drama", "Fantasy"]
  }
}
3. Implementation Options
JSON Server (Mock API): Create a db.json file in the project to simulate a REST API.
Supabase / Firebase: Use a Backend-as-a-Service for real-time data.
Local SQLite: Simple SQL file for a backend server (Node/Python).
